SENATE BILL 816
C8 6lr1763
CF 6lr1762
By: Senator Hayes
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Finance
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 West North Avenue Development Authority – Neighborhood Social Connection
3 and Development Program – Establishment
4 (WNADA Neighborhood Social Connection and Development Act)
5 FOR the purpose of establishing the Neighborhood Social Connection and Development
6 Program within the West North Avenue Development Authority to provide technical
7 support and grants to certain organizations to implement programs that foster social
8 connections and activities in a certain area; and generally relating to the
9 Neighborhood Social Connection and Development Program in the West North
10 Avenue Development Authority.
11 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
12 Article – Economic Development
13 Section 12–701
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY adding to
17 Article – Economic Development
18 Section 12–715
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
23 Article – Economic Development
24 12–701.
25 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0816*

2 SENATE BILL 816
1 (b) “Authority” means the West North Avenue Development Authority.
2 (c) “Board” means the Board of Directors of the Authority.
3 (d) “Buffer zone” means the area within 250 yards of the target area.
4 (e) “Target area” means the portion of West North Avenue in Baltimore City
5 between the 600 block and the 3200 block, inclusive.
6 (f) “West North Avenue Corridor” includes the geographic area consisting of the
7 target area and the buffer zone.
8 12–715.
9 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PROGRAM” MEANS THE NEIGHBORHOOD SOCIAL
10 CONNECTION AND DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM.
11 (B) THERE IS A NEIGHBORHOOD SOCIAL CONNECTION AND DEVELOPMENT
12 PROGRAM IN THE AUTHORITY.
13 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO FOSTER SOCIAL CONNECTIONS
14 TO SUPPORT NEIGHBORHOOD DEVELOPMENT WITHIN THE WEST NORTH AVENUE
15 CORRIDOR BY:
16 (1) PROVIDING TECHNICAL SUPPORT TO PARTICIPATING
17 ORGANIZATIONS, INCLUDING COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT CORPORATIONS,
18 NEIGHBORHOOD ASSOCIATIONS, VOLUNTEER GROUPS, AND NONPROFIT
19 ORGANIZATIONS; AND
20 (2) AWARDING GRANTS TO IMPLEMENT PROGRAMS THAT FOSTER
21 SOCIAL CONNECTIONS AND ACTIVITIES TAILORED TO SUPPORT NEIGHBORHOOD
22 DEVELOPMENT.
23 (D) (1) THE AUTHORITY SHALL AWARD GRANTS TO IMPLEMENT THE
24 PROGRAM.
25 (2) THE AUTHORITY MAY SET ASIDE EXISTING FUNDS OF NOT MORE
26 THAN $500,000 FOR THE PURPOSE OF AWARDING GRANTS UNDER THE PROGRAM.
27 (3) THE AUTHORITY MAY AWARD A GRANT UNDER THIS SECTION
28 ONLY FOR:

SENATE BILL 816 3
1 (I) SOCIAL GATHERINGS, INCLUDING BLOCK PARTIES,
2 CULTURAL FESTIVALS, PARADES, SPEAKER SERIES, AND SERVICE OR
3 RECREATIONAL EVENTS;
4 (II) OUTREACH INITIATIVES, INCLUDING NEIGHBORHOOD
5 NEWSLETTERS, COMMUNITY BULLETINS, OR DIGITAL CONTENT, TO RAISE
6 AWARENESS OF SOCIAL EVENTS AND CONNECT RESIDENTS WITH AVAILABLE
7 RESOURCES AND SERVICES;
8 (III) STIPENDS TO COMPENSATE VOLUNTEERS FOR THE TIME
9 USED TO ORGANIZE PROJECTS, REFRESHMENTS AT PROGRAM DESIGNATED
10 EVENTS, RENTAL AND EVENT SPACES, AND MATERIALS FOR PROGRAM EVENTS;
11 (IV) OPERATING SUPPORT FOR PARTICIPATING
12 ORGANIZATIONS;
13 (V) SOCIAL CONNECTION PROJECTS TO CREATE AND MAINTAIN
14 GREEN SPACES OR OTHER COMMUNITY GATHERING SPACES;
15 (VI) RESOURCES FOR TRAINING AND HIRING COMMUNITY
16 ORGANIZERS; AND
17 (VII) RESOURCES FOR GRANT APPLICATION EFFORTS.
18 (E) PARTICIPATING ORGANIZATIONS SHALL COLLABORATE WITH
19 RESIDENTS OF THE WEST NORTH AVENUE CORRIDOR IN THE PLANNING AND
20 IMPLEMENTATION OF EVENTS AND PROJECTS TO ENSURE THAT ACTIVITIES
21 REFLECT NEIGHBORHOOD PRIORITIES AND, TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, THAT
22 EVENTS AND ACTIVITIES ARE LED BY RESIDENTS.
23 (F) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2029, THE AUTHORITY SHALL COMPILE
24 EVALUATIONS AND OUTCOMES OF PROGRAMS TO DEVELOP A TEMPLATE FOR
25 NEIGHBORHOOD BUILDING AND PROVIDE SCALING RECOMMENDATIONS TO SIMILAR
26 ORGANIZATIONS IN THE STATE AND ACROSS THE UNITED STATES.
27 (G) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1, 2027, AND EACH DECEMBER 1
28 THEREAFTER, THE AUTHORITY SHALL REPORT TO THE GOVERNOR AND, IN
29 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE GENERAL
30 ASSEMBLY ON ITS COMPREHENSIVE GRANT–AWARDING ACTIVITIES.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
32 October 1, 2026. It shall remain effective until the taking effect of the termination provision
33 specified in Section 3 of Chapters 215 and 216 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025.
34 If that termination provision takes effect, this Act, with no further action required by the

4 SENATE BILL 816
1 General Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect. This Act may not
2 be interpreted to have any effect on that termination provision.

